The paper deals with natural language question answering using memory networks and universal schema, which are techniques commonly used in the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves reasoning on knowledge bases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR) from unstructured text. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely for this paper.
